{
  "doc_id": "19392",
  "text": "In our previous research, three norfriedelins with acetylcholinesterase inhibitory activity were found in acerola tree (M. emarginata) [CITATION_1] . As continuation of this work, we have examined the lipophilic constituents of aerial parts of acerola collected in Nanning, Guangxi Province, China. Three new tetranorditerpenes (1-3) with a rare 2H-benz[e]inden-2-one substructure were obtained ( Figure 1 ). This report describes the isolation and structural determination of the compounds, as well as their cytotoxic activities. ",
